ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The decline in measles vaccination is understandable in the face of the COVID-19 pandemic that is taking all the attention of care providers and supporting laboratories.

The decline in measles vaccination before the pandemic is not. It would be important to understand where the barriers are to effective vaccination that would bring coverage up to the needed 95%. One hopes that once the current COVID-19 pandemic has subsided, attention and efforts will again turn to bringing the percentages of children vaccinated up to the levels necessary to avoid cases and outbreaks of that disease. - Mod.TY]
